        Ben Bitdiddle, an expert systems programmer, looks over Alyssas
        shoulder and comments that it is not clear what it means to
        divide by an interval that spans zero.  Modify Alyssas program to
        check for this condition and to signal an error if it occurs.



  mul_interval
  upper_bound
  div_interval_example


function div_interval(x, y) {
    if(lower_bound(y) <= 0 && upper_bound(y) >= 0) {
        error("Division error (interval spans 0)", y);
    } else {
        return mul_interval(x, make_interval(1.0 / upper_bound(y),
                                         1.0 / lower_bound(y)));
    }
}

